---
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHeader from '~/components/PageHeader.astro';
import DividerText from '~/components/DividerText.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Formatting Showcase"
  description="A standalone page that demonstrates common article formatting and UI sections."
>
  <PageHeader title="Formatting Showcase" />

  <article class="prose py-7.5" data-pagefind-body>
    <p>
      This page is a compact reference for the visual pieces a post might need: headings,
      copy blocks, lists, code, tables, callouts, cards, media, and action sections.
    </p>

    <DividerText text="Typography" />

    <h1>Heading One</h1>
    <p>
      Use a top-level heading for the main idea. Keep paragraphs short enough to scan,
      especially when the surrounding page already has navigation and metadata.
    </p>

    <h2>Heading Two</h2>
    <p>
      Inline code like <code>useSyncExternalStore</code>, <code>getSnapshot</code>, and
      <code>subscribe</code> should stand out without becoming louder than the sentence.
    </p>

    <h3>Heading Three</h3>
    <p>
      Links should feel obvious in running text, like <a href="/">the home page</a>, but
      not break the reading rhythm.
    </p>

    <blockquote>
      <p>
        A good callout should slow the reader down for one useful idea, not become a
        second article inside the article.
      </p>
    </blockquote>

    <DividerText text="Lists" />

    <p>Use unordered lists for related ideas:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>Short, scannable points</li>
      <li>One idea per bullet</li>
      <li>No fake hierarchy unless it actually helps</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Use ordered lists for sequence:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>Read the current value.</li>
      <li>Subscribe to changes.</li>
      <li>Render again when the value changes.</li>
    </ol>

    <DividerText text="Code" />

    <p>Small code examples should be complete enough to understand on their own.</p>

    <pre><code>{`function createCounter() {
  let count = 0;

  return {
    get() {
      return count;
    },
    increment() {
      count++;
    },
  };
}`}</code></pre>

    <p>Terminal output should be visually separate from source code.</p>

    <pre><code>{`$ node counter.js
count: 1
count: 2`}</code></pre>

    <DividerText text="Tables" />

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Pattern</th>
          <th>Use When</th>
          <th>Skip When</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>useState</code></td>
          <td>React owns the value</td>
          <td>The source lives outside React</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>useContext</code></td>
          <td>React passes shared value down</td>
          <td>You need subscriptions to an external store</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>useSyncExternalStore</code></td>
          <td>React reads external state</td>
          <td>It is just local UI state</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <DividerText text="Callouts" />

    <section class="grid gap-4 not-prose">
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-blue/30 bg-blue/8 p-4">
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-blue">Note</h2>
        <p class="m-0 text-sm/6">
          Use this for context that helps, but does not need to interrupt the main flow.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-green/30 bg-green/8 p-4">
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-green">Tip</h2>
        <p class="m-0 text-sm/6">
          Use this for practical advice the reader can apply immediately.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-yellow/30 bg-yellow/8 p-4">
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-lg font-semibold text-yellow">Caution</h2>
        <p class="m-0 text-sm/6">
          Use this when a small mistake can make an example confusing or misleading.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <DividerText text="Cards" />

    <section class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 not-prose">
      <article class="rounded-xl border-2 border-foreground/10 p-4">
        <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-foreground/70">Concept</p>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-heading2">Snapshot</h2>
        <p class="text-sm/6">
          The value React reads from an external source during render.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-xl border-2 border-foreground/10 p-4">
        <p class="mb-2 text-sm text-foreground/70">Contract</p>
        <h2 class="mb-2 text-xl font-semibold text-heading2">Subscribe</h2>
        <p class="text-sm/6">
          The function that tells React when the external value may have changed.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <DividerText text="Media" />

    <figure>
      <div
        class="flex aspect-video items-center justify-center rounded-xl border-8 border-foreground/10 bg-accent/8 text-center text-accent"
      >
        Image or demo preview
      </div>
      <figcaption>A caption should explain why the visual exists.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <DividerText text="Actions" />

    <section class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 not-prose">
      <a class="button" href="/">Primary link</a>
      <a class="button" href="/posts">Archive link</a>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
